video._emit('play');
// assert send.calls.length === 1
```

Hmm, that part is the "解绑前" check, which passed. So the FIRST emit works.

Then unbind, then:
```js
send.clear();
video._emit('play');
video._emit('pause');
video._emit('seeked');
assert.strictEqual(send.calls.length, 0, ...);  // FAILED: actual 1
```

The actual was 1. So one of the emits did call send. Which one? Probably 'play' or 'pause' or 'seeked'.

Hmm, let me check again. Wait - I just realized. The `_emit` looks up `_listeners[event]`. After `delete _listeners[event]`, the lookup returns undefined, so nothing happens. That's correct.

But the test failed with actual=1. So one of the listeners was NOT removed.

Wait, I bet there's a name collision. Let me re-read carefu...

